{
  "doc_id": "36231",
  "text": "Although a number of studies on the association between CRT and malignant tumors have been conducted, the findings concerning the level and significance of CRT expression in cancer are not consistent in different types of tumors. Previous studies have demonstrated that CRT is upregulated in oral squamous cell carcinoma (11), pancreatic cancer [CITATION_1] , breast cancer (15), hepatocellular carcinoma (17), adrenocortical carcinomas [CITATION_2] and gastric cancer [CITATION_3] . However, the results of a previous study by the present authors indicated that CRT was downregulated in osteosarcoma cells [CITATION_4] . In the present study, immunofluorescent staining, RT-qPCR and western blotting were conducted to detect the expression of CRT in Saos-2 osteosarcoma cells following culture with DATS at different concentrations and exposure times.",
